The onMenuItemSelect callback in script always return 0 for itemId. I run a debug session and when I break the code when the onMenuItemSelect_callback is sent, the item->id is correct but the Con::getIntArg return 0 to the script

```
onMenuItemSelect_callback(Con::getIntArg(menu->id), menu->text, Con::getIntArg(item->id), item->text);
```

I fixed it by changing the callback itemId field to S32 and I also quickly test to confirm my issue with:

```
IMPLEMENT_CALLBACK(GuiMenuBar, onMenuItemSelect, void, (const char* menuId, const char* menuText, const char*  menuItemId, const char* menuItemText), ...
IMPLEMENT_CALLBACK(GuiMenuBar, onMenuItemSelectFix, void, (const char* menuId, const char* menuText, S32 menuItemId, const char* menuItemText),...
static const char *test;
    test = Con::getIntArg(item->id);
    if (item->enabled){
        onMenuItemSelectFix_callback(Con::getIntArg(menu->id), menu->text, (S32)item->id, item->text);
        onMenuItemSelect_callback(Con::getIntArg(menu->id), menu->text, Con::getIntArg(item->id), test);
    }
```

My Fixed callback return the correct ID but not the default callback. The test var also return 0 to the script but when I check the value in debug, I get '2' (for itemId 2). I'm not sure what's going wrong since the menu->id is sent correctly

